Reservoirs on Songhua River reinforce water discharge to dilute pollution slick.
The discharging move was made with the approval by the State
The Fengman Hydropower Station in the upper reach of Songhua
River increased the daily discharge amount from 600 cubic meters per second to 1,000 cubic meters per second starting from 10:00 Thursday.
The flow is expected to return to 600 cubic meters per second in the evening.
The toxic contents in the water are declining after days of sedimentation, experts said, citing water monitoring statistics.
Heilongjiang Province local environment authority said.
